# Snyk policy file — https://docs.snyk.io/snyk-cli/test-for-vulnerabilities/the-.snyk-file
#
# The `5dive-cli` skill is flagged CRITICAL E006 "malicious code pattern detected
# in skill scripts". This is a FALSE POSITIVE:
#   * The skill contains NO executable scripts — it is SKILL.md + reference
#     markdown only. There is nothing to execute.
#   * The heuristic trips on PROSE that documents the intended, dual-use
#     capabilities of a first-party agent-orchestration CLI (inter-agent
#     messaging, operator-scoped credential provisioning, first-party
#     self-update). All operate solely within one operator's own trust boundary.
#   * See SECURITY.md for the full trust model and threat analysis.
#
# A false-positive dispute has been filed with the scanner. This suppression is
# transparent and on-record — it does NOT obfuscate or alter any code.
version: v1.25.0
ignore:
  E006:
    - '*':
        reason: >-
          False positive. 5dive-cli is a documentation-only skill (SKILL.md +
          reference markdown, no executable scripts). The flagged patterns are
          prose describing first-party agent-orchestration features that operate
          only within a single operator's own fleet. See SECURITY.md.
        expires: 2027-07-03T00:00:00.000Z
patch: {}
